# homedash-go — IDE Rules

## Project Type
Go 1.21 backend + HTML/CSS/JS frontend
Single dependency: fsnotify (file watching)

## Code Style
- Use `slog` for logging (not `log` or `fmt`)
- Exported: `CamelCase`, unexported: `camelCase`
- Early returns, no nested if-else
- `RLock` for reads, `Lock` for writes, always `defer Unlock`
- All long operations accept `context.Context`
- No global state (except `adminRateLimiter`)
- Thread-safe: `sync.RWMutex` for all state operations

## Testing
- Table-driven tests where possible
- Tests in `*_test.go` files
- Run: `go test ./...`

## File Structure
- `main.go` — entry point
- `app.go` — DI, routing, middleware, config watcher
- `handlers.go` — HTTP handlers
- `checks.go` — service health checks
- `config.go` — config management
- `metrics.go` — metrics, circuit breaker
- `icons.go` — icon mapping
- `types.go` — data structures
- `templates/` — HTML templates
- `static/` — CSS/JS assets

## Important Notes
- Config hot-reload via fsnotify with 500ms debounce
- Circuit breaker: 3 failures → open → probe after 30s
- Worker pool: 20 concurrent workers
- Cache: 3s TTL + stale-while-revalidate (15s max)
- Rate limiter: 20 burst, 10 requests/second for admin

## Docker
- Multi-stage build (alpine)
- Non-privileged user (UID 1000)
- Healthcheck: wget to /health
- Port: 5000 (configurable via HOMEDASH_PORT)

## Common Commands
```bash
go run main.go          # Run locally
go build -o homedash .  # Build
go test ./...           # Run tests
golangci-lint run       # Lint (if installed)
go vet ./...            # Vet
```
